{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc39723b9-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3690"},"text":"§ 3690.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Overcharges by educational institutions; discontinuance of allowances; examination of records; false or misleading statements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc39723ba-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Overcharges by Educational Institutions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"If the Secretary finds that an educational institution has—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723bb-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" charged or received from any eligible veteran or eligible person pursuing a program of education under this chapter or chapter 34 or 35 of this title any amount for any course in excess of the charges for tuition and fees which such institution requires similarly circumstanced nonveterans not receiving assistance under such chapters who are enrolled in the same course to pay, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723bc-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" instituted, after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-24"},"text":"October 24, 1972","children":[],"tail":", a policy or practice with respect to the payment of tuition, fees, or other charges in the case of eligible veterans and the Secretary finds that the effect of such policy or practice substantially denies to veterans the benefits of the advance allowances under such section,"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"the Secretary may disapprove such educational institution for the enrollment of any eligible veteran or eligible person not already enrolled therein under this chapter or chapter 31, 34, or 35 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc39723bd-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Discontinuance of Allowances","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723be-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary may discontinue the educational assistance allowance of any eligible veteran or eligible person if the Secretary finds that the program of education or any course in which the veteran or person is enrolled fails to meet any of the requirements of this chapter or chapter 34 or 35 of this title, or if the Secretary finds that the educational institution offering such program or course has violated any provision of this chapter or chapter 34 or 35 of this title, or fails to meet any of the requirements of such chapters.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723bf-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection, any action by the Secretary under paragraph (1) of this subsection to discontinue (including to suspend) assistance provided to any eligible veteran or eligible person under this chapter or chapter 31, 32, 34, or 35 of this title shall be based upon evidence that the veteran or eligible person is not or was not entitled to such assistance. Whenever the Secretary so discontinues any such assistance, the Secretary shall concurrently provide written notice to such veteran or person of such discontinuance and that such veteran or person is entitled thereafter to a statement of the reasons for such action and an opportunity to be heard thereon.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c0-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c1-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary may suspend educational assistance to eligible veterans and eligible persons already enrolled, and may disapprove the enrollment or reenrollment of any eligible veteran or eligible person, in any course as to which the Secretary has evidence showing a substantial pattern of eligible veterans or eligible persons, or both, who are receiving such assistance by virtue of their enrollment in such course but who are not entitled to such assistance because (i) the course approval requirements of this chapter are not being met, or (ii) the educational institution offering such course has violated one or more of the recordkeeping or reporting requirements of this chapter or chapter 30, 32, 33, 34, or 35 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c2-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Action may be taken under subparagraph (A) of this paragraph only after—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c3-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/3/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary provides to the State approving agency concerned and the educational institution concerned written notice of any such failure to meet such approval requirements and any such violation of such recordkeeping or reporting requirements;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c4-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/3/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such institution refuses to take corrective action or does not within 60 days after such notice (or within such longer period as the Secretary determines is reasonable and appropriate) take corrective action; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c5-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/b/3/B/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary, not less than 30 days before taking action under such subparagraph, provides to each eligible veteran and eligible person already enrolled in such course written notice of the Secretary’s intent to take such action (and the reasons therefor) unless such corrective action is taken within such 60 days (or within such longer period as the Secretary has determined is reasonable and appropriate), and of the date on which the Secretary intends to take action under such subparagraph.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c6-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Examination of Records","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c7-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in paragraph (2), notwithstanding any other provision of law, the records and accounts of educational institutions pertaining to eligible veterans or eligible persons who received educational assistance under this chapter or chapter 31, 32, 34, or 35 of this title, as well as the records of other students which the Secretary determines necessary to ascertain institutional compliance with the requirements of such chapters, shall be available for examination by duly authorized representatives of the Government.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c8-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Paragraph (1) does not apply to the records and accounts—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723c9-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an educational institution located in a foreign country; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idc39723ca-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that pertain to an individual who is not receiving educational assistance under this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc39723cb-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3690/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"False or Misleading Statements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Whenever the Secretary finds that an educational institution has willfully submitted a false or misleading claim, or that a veteran or person, with the complicity of an educational institution, has submitted such a claim, the Secretary shall make a complete report of the facts of the case to the appropriate State approving agency and, where deemed advisable, to the Attorney General of the United States for appropriate action.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc39723cc-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/540/tIII/s316/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–540, title III, § 316(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-24"},"text":"Oct. 24, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1088"},"text":"86 Stat. 1088","children":[],"tail":", § 1790; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/502/tV"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–502, title V","children":[],"tail":", §§ 510, 513(a)(19), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2401"},"text":"90 Stat. 2401","children":[],"tail":", 2403; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/202/tIII/s306"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–202, title III, § 306","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-11-23"},"text":"Nov. 23, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1445"},"text":"91 Stat. 1445","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466/tVIII/s801/f"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–466, title VIII, § 801(f)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2216"},"text":"94 Stat. 2216","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/295/s4/59"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–295, § 4(59)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1309"},"text":"96 Stat. 1309","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/306/tII/s207"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–306, title II, § 207","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1435"},"text":"96 Stat. 1435","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/237/tIV/s423/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–237, title IV, § 423(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", (b)(1)(A), (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2092"},"text":"103 Stat. 2092","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 3690, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","a